body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Char's Counterattack]] from 1988.

An extensive modification of the [[Geara Doga]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] for Newtype use. The two units produced were equipped with shields doubling as funnel pods on each arm and special armament for each of them - the unit piloted by Cyber-Newtype [[Gyunei Guss]] was painted a bluish green with yellow accents and possessed a more pronounced antenna on its head, and was furnished with a powerful beam assault rifle equipped with a grenade launcher.

[spoiler]Unlike Quess's Jagd Doga, Gyunei's does not survive -  after challenging [[Amuro Ray]]'s bluff, he is mercilessly crushed by the [[Nu Gundam]]'s Fin Funnels, believing they were just radiator fins.[/spoiler]

title: arched_crown
body:
A [[crown]] consisting of multiple metallic arches converging where the orb of the crown, or [i]monde[/i], would be at the very top. The arches may or may not be [[jeweled crown|lined with gems]]. The crown's [i]cross[/i], located atop the monde, would either be an actual cross to represent the Christian influence of monarchies, or can possess a different shape. The crown's [i]cap[/i] is lined with velvet that has a ermine base, although there are arched crowns with no cap present. Red velvet is typical of real-like royal crowns, and are frequently the basic depiction for arched crowns in artwork.

title: owata-ko
body:
The nickname of a player character in a "'Let's Play' video series" uploaded on [[NicoNico]] called "Let's Play [[Fallout 3]] PC Edition with a Little Girl, Owata-style". She is a [[blonde hair]]ed girl with [[twintails]] and she wears a variety of clothes that are not at all suited for combat.

オワタ式 ([i]owata-shiki[/i], owata-style) in Japanese game slang carries the same meaning as "sudden death-style" and refers to a style of play in which "MODs":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mod_%28video_gaming%29 and hidden commands are used to fix the player character's hit points at "1". "Owata" comes from "[i][[\(^o^)/|Jinsei Owata]][/i]".

There are several unique points in this "sexy" play video made by "JAX.":http://www.nicovideo.jp/user/560733 

* A MOD is used to turn "Vault101のアイツ (Vault 101 [i]no Aitsu[/i], Dat Dude from Vault 101)" (a nickname for the "Lone Wanderer":http://fallout.wikia.com/wiki/Lone_Wanderer in Japan) into a little girl. (Instructions for installing the MOD are explained in "the video creator's blog.":http://owatakogaippai.blog117.fc2.com/ )
* A MOD is installed for modifying attack power. The attack power is about three times that of normal.
* A MOD is used to increase a portion of the number of enemies by up to five times.
* The gore setting is always OFF.

This video series ended on "Part.25":http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm10508206 while being well received. The total number of deaths was 380 times.

In this video, there was "a scene":http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm9784985 where Owata-ko was saved from danger by the "Mysterious Stranger":http://fallout.wikia.com/wiki/Mysterious_Stranger called forth by her "perk.":http://fallout.wikia.com/wiki/Perk Judging from the stranger's dubious appearance, viewers of the series posted joke comments saying "that is definitely JAX's personal avatar". Also, near "the close of the game,":http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm10106865 her little sister appears as a "companion":http://fallout.wikia.com/wiki/Companion and JAX simply called her [[Owata-ko 2]].

After that, he created a sequel titled "Let's Play [[Fallout: New Vegas]] PC Edition, Owata-style" that was concluded on April 28, 2011. The main character of this video was a girl with [[silver hair]] called [[Owata-ko 3]] but, unfortunately, she ended up being erased when the game's saved data was lost in "Part.6.":http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm12786814 From there on, he returned to the starting point and re-introduced the original Owata-ko.

h4. See also

He has "defeated" the government around the world and subdued them, thus allows him to do whatever he wished with little to no consequence. title: corrupted_mynah_(signalis)
body:
[[Mynah (Signalis)|Mynahs]] in their [[Zombie|corrupted state]]. These are the most dangerous variety of enemy encountered in [[Signalis]], and are most notably used as the first boss encounter in the game.

h6. Appearance
Corrupted Mynahs are the least diverged from their non-corrupted counterparts, only bearing a covering of [[blood|oxidant fluid]] [[blood on armor|on their armor]], particularly around the [[blood on hands|hands]], arms, and [[blood on chest|chest]]. Corrupted Mynahs typically have their [[face shield|face shields]] closed most of the time, but will occasionally open it in order to [[vomiting blood|release]] a flow of oxidant fluid and [[worm|worms]] from the cavity containing their face. Interestingly, according to the boss intro cutscene, corrupted Mynahs still have their faces intact, unlike every other corrupted replika seen in game.

title: japanese_crested_ibis_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The [[crested_ibis|Japanese Crested Ibis]] or Toki ([i]Nipponia nippon[/i]) is a large bird with a mostly white plumage, a bare head, showing red skin and a crest of white feathers on the nape. The japanese name for this bird ("Toki") is also used to refer to the Ibis group as a whole.

Crested Ibis (the Friend) has long, swept back white hair (resembling the bird's crest) which turns red at her sidelocks and [[head wings]], with [[blunt bangs]]. She wears a white jacket with red [[feather-trimmed sleeves]], a red [[pleated skirt]], and red pantyhose. Her eyes are yellow and she wears red gloves.
As her species were bought back from the brink of extinction (and were thought for some time as being extinct), she exibits [[empty_eyes|the lack of shine on the eyes]] usually reserved to extinct species.

She is best described as a terrible singer who likes to sing nonetheless. In the anime, she typically sings about where are her friends (her infamous "WATASHI WA TOOOKIIII" song) with a shrill voice that can stun most Friends (as poor [[Serval (kemono_friends)|]] can attest). A serving of [[Alpaca Suri (kemono_friends)|]]'s tea improves her voice to a certain extent (she can't stun anyone by singing).

She is often associated with another [[Toki (hokuto_no_ken)|]] (whom is also at the brink of death).

title: kirimon_(paulownia)
body:
Kirimon (桐紋) means "paulownia crest". It consists of 3 leaves with a set of flowers rising from each. It is the crest of the Toyotomi clan and was later adopted for use by the Japanese government.

h4. Variations
There are many variations of the crest. One of the most important distinctions is the number of flowers shown. Variations with 5-7-5 flowers (五七桐 go-shichi no kiri) are usually considered the highest status. Examples:
* the Toyotomi clan
* the Prime Minister of Japan
* Government Seal of Japan 

Variations with 3-5-3 flowers (五三桐 gosan kiri, 5-3 paulownia) are the most common [1]. "It is found in the emblem of the Ministry of Justice and the Imperial Guard Headquarters. According to a study by Japan Kamon Society, about 70% of the paulownia crests use 'Maru ni go-san kiri' (丸に五三桐), a roundel of the 5-3 Paulownia." [1]

title: fasces_(object)
body:
[B]Fasces[/b] is an object or [[heraldry|heraldic]] symbol that consists of a bound wooden rod bundle, often incorporating an axe (occasionally two) with its blade emerging. It is an Italian symbol that had its origin in the Etruscan civilization and was passed on to ancient Rome, representing law, power and governance.

During the first half of 20th century, the fasces became the symbol of National Fascist Party of Italy (origin of the term [i][[fascist|fascism]][/i]).

title: toyota_sprinter_trueno
body:
The Toyota Sprinter Trueno is a small, lightweight coupe introduced by Toyota in 1983 as part of the fifth generation Toyota Corolla lineup. The insider-chassis code of "AE86" depicts the 1600 cc rear-wheel drive model from the range. The Levin has fixed-headlights, and the Trueno has retractable headlights, both could be hatchback or coupe. The export model name Corolla covers both variations. 

The car is best known for its incredible handling characteristic, which leads into it being frequently used in various [[drifting|drift]] [[racing]] tournaments.

This tag also covers the AE85 (sold as the Toyota Corolla Levin, Toyota Sprinter Trueno or Toyota Corolla DX), likewise a rear-wheel drive sports coupe, manufactured by Toyota from 1983-1987. While the AE85 shares its chassis and basic design with the famous AE86, the AE85 was designed for economy and differs mainly in its engine, compared to the AE86, which was designed for performance.

The white and black color variant (informally known as the "panda" Trueno) is most known as [[Fujiwara Takumi]]'s [[fujiwara takumi's toyota trueno ae86|'Tofu Delivery' car]] from the [[Initial D]] series, while [[Takeuchi Itsuki]] purchases an AE85 Levin, mistaken for an AE86. Later on, a young man by the name of [[Inui Shinji]] appears, driving a notchback late-model Trueno.

h4. See also

* "Wikipedia: Toyota Corolla Levin and Toyota Sprinter Trueno":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_Corolla_Levin_and_Toyota_Sprinter_Trueno]
* "Wikipedia: Toyota AE86":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_AE86
* "Wikipedia: Toyota AE85":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_AE85

title: u.n._spacy
body:
The [b]U.N. Spacy[/b] (United Nations [[Space]] Navy) is the fictional [[military]] arm of the Earth U.N. Government (地球統合政府 [i]"Chikyuu Tougou Seifu"[/i]) in the [[Macross]] Japanese anime series.

The organization's name is derived from words [b]SPAC[/b]E and NAV[b]Y[/b], therefore, combining them to make the word [b]SPACY[/b]. 

In the Macross chronology it was established after 1999 by the successor to the modern [[United Nations]] in order to defend Earth from a possible attack by hostile [[alien]]s.

However, from 1999 to 2008 the U.N. Spacy was also involved in the [[Macross Zero|U.N. Wars]] conflict, fighting against a human [[Anti-U.N.]] faction opposed to the formation of the worldwide U.N. government. 

A year later (2009) the U.N. Spacy was involved in the subsequent [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross|Space War I]], defending our planet from an hostile extraterrestrial race called the [[Zentradi]]. Later operations of the U.N. Spacy expanded into interstellar colonization and general peacekeeping of off-world Earth settlements.

At the time of the Zentradi invasion, the U.N. Spacy's assets included military bases on Earth, the [[Moon]] and [[Mars (planet)|]], squadrons of variable fighters and other [[mecha]], several capital [[spacecraft]] in orbit and the repaired SDF-1 [i]Macross[/i] on South Ataria Island, the flagship of the United Nations Spacy.

The U.N. Spacy was succeeded by the [b]New U.N. Spacy[/b] ([[N.U.N.S.]]).  

In the [[ROBOTECH]] western adaptation the U.N. Spacy is reimagined as the actual space navy component of the [b]Robotech Defense Force (R.D.F.)[/b].

title: triceratops_fist
body:
A [[martial arts]] technique used by [[Hanma Baki]] from [[Grappler Baki]], first conceived during his fight against the prehistoric caveman [[Pickle (grappler_baki)|]].

To use this technique, the user takes one step forward, lowers their upper body, and juts their fists forward, with one fist above and one below their head somewhat akin to a [[triceratops]]' horns. With this stance, the user is capable of parrying the opponent's attack, as well as performing a powerful charge at the same time.

Parodies of this stance often have the silhouette of a [[triceratops]] behind the user, in reference to when this technique was used for the first time by Baki.

A meticulous and attentive student of [[Kal'tsit (Arknights)|]] who officially became involved in field medical missions after a half-year of preparatory training. Unlike conventional medics, she actively looks for opportunities to attack the enemy through the use of various drug compounds.

One of the protagonists in the side story event [i]Twilight of Wolumonde[/i]. Very easily agitated and prone to shouting at others as shown in the side story and her multiple in-game lines. Also holds deep grudges against the Ursus Empire due to abhorrent living conditions she suffered under and deems them to be the ones responsible for the disappearance of her family.

Her motif is based on the [[mongoose]]. Her callsign is derived from [i]Folinic acid[/i], noted to be the first word she could not remember in a medical dictionary.

body:
An ocean-themed unit in [[hololive]] consisting of [[Houshou Marine]], [[Minato Aqua]], [[Ninomae Ina'nis]], [[Gawr Gura]], and [[Sakamata Chloe]]. 

[i]UMISEA[/i] is an official hololive unit meant to bring together [[virtual Youtuber|virtual YouTubers]] in the production with a common ocean theme and lore under a common name.

Has released a group single in 2021 alongside on-stream collabs in [[Minecraft]] and other games. The aforementioned Minecraft collab streams also showed that the two [[hololive English]] members (Ina and Gura) were inducted into [[AKUKIN Kensetsu]] (though jokingly, Gura temporarily became its CEO for the duration of their collab).

body:
A straight-armed [[cross]] that was the emblem of the [i][[Wehrmacht]][/i] and its branches, the [i]Heer[/i] (army), the [i][[Kriegsmarine]][/i] (navy), and the [i][[Luftwaffe]][/i] (air force), during [[World War II]]. Often appearing on [[military vehicle]]s.

The [i]Balkenkreuz[/b] appears to be a thick black cross with arms of equal length, surrounded with white outline.

title: boeing_737_max
body:
A twin-engine narrow-body airliner manufactured by American aerospace manufacturer [[Boeing]], designed as a competitor to the Airbus A320neo.

The latest development of the [[boeing 737|737]] family, it features more fuel efficient [[jet engine|engines]] with noise-reducing chevrons, redesigned winglets, as well as the [b]Maneuvering Characteristics Augmentation System[/b] ("MCAS":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maneuvering_Characteristics_Augmentation_System).

It has also had a troubled history involving two crashes in "2018":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_Air_Flight_610 and "2019":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopian_Airlines_Flight_302 caused by sudden activation of the MCAS which killed 346 people, and an "incident in early 2024":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska_Airlines_Flight_1282 where a door plug on the side of the plane blew off mid flight.

The titular character of the [[John Wick]] series.

A former assassin of the underground secret society known as the Continental, John was renowned as one of the deadliest men alive, and was so feared that the Russian Mafia called him "Baba Yaga", after the legendary bogeyman figure from Russian folklore. 

When tragic circumstances lead to the son of a local Russian mob boss making a very dire enemy of John, every member of the local criminal underworld soon learns just how bad a mistake setting off John Wick actually is.

He is protrayed by [[Keanu Reeves]].
